[thinking] **Analyzing class loader conflicts**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m exploring module conflicts, specifically if the same installer appears in both a named module and unnamed. It seems that if a package exists in both, like `reactor.blockhound.shaded.net.bytebuddy.agent`, the named module doesn’t read the unnamed one unless I add the appropriate reads. I wonder about class loaders too: the PlatformClassLoader serves as a parent. So, if the app loader has a dependency and loads its own version of an Installer, it could lead to duplicate class issues. JPMS might allow this if they’re under different loaders. That’s interesting!
[thinking] 
