JPMS might allow this if they’re under different loaders. That’s interesting!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying module dependencies**\\n\\nI’m thinking about class loaders and their delegation to the boot or platform class loader. I need to consider if a module requires all packages from its dependencies. For instance, if I’m using `reactor.blockhound.shaded.net.bytebuddy.jar.asm` within the same module, that seems straightforward. But, what about dependencies like `java.desktop`? Since Byte Buddy uses `java.beans.Introspector`, I should probably add a requirement for `java.desktop`, as well as `java.sql`. That makes sense!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_lJMHnqHLXGxGhZCNbSWzMgVl|fc_086c6b24cd8e49e4016a293cd943ec819599f8fe7b9c7feea3", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "tmp=$(mktemp -d); mkdir -p \"$tmp/src/reactor/blockhound/shaded/net/bytebuddy/agent/builder\" \"$tmp/out\"; cat > \"$tmp/src/module-info.java\" <<'EOF'\nmodule blockhound.bytebuddy.agentbuilder.copy {\n    requires java.desktop;\n    requires java.instrument;\n    requires java.logging;\n    requires java.management;\n    requires java.naming;\n    requires java.sql;\n    requires java.xml;\n    requires jdk.unsupported;\n    exports reactor.blockhound.shaded.net.bytebuddy.agent.builder;\n}\nEOF\ncat > \"$tmp/src/reactor/blockhound/shaded/net/bytebuddy/agent/builder/Placeholder.java\" <<'EOF'\npackage reactor.blockhound.shaded.net.bytebuddy.agent.builder;\npublic class Placeholder {}\nEOF\njavac --release 9 -d \"$tmp/out\" \"$tmp/src/module-info.java\" \"$tmp/src/reactor/blockhound/shaded/net/bytebuddy/agent/builder/Placeholder.java\" && base64 -w0 \"$tmp/out/module-info.class\"; rm -rf \"$tmp\"", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 857, "output": 956, "cacheRead": 31744, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 33557, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopR